# Demand Intelligence Decision Flow

The Demand Intelligence Platform converts raw demand signals into actionable forecasts that power operational and financial decisions across commerce systems.

The system integrates demand signals, machine learning forecasting models and planning workflows to generate accurate demand projections.

## Demand Forecast Generation

Demand signals from multiple sources are aggregated and transformed into forecasting features.

Inputs include:

• Historical sales  
• Traffic signals  
• Promotions and campaigns  
• Seasonality and calendar events  
• Product attributes  

These signals feed into forecasting models which generate SKU-level demand projections.

## Forecast Consumption

Demand forecasts power several downstream planning systems across the commerce ecosystem.

Inventory Planning  
Forecasts determine optimal inventory levels across warehouses.

Replenishment Planning  
Demand signals trigger replenishment recommendations.

Supply Planning  
Forecasts guide vendor purchasing and production planning.

Capacity Planning  
Demand projections support warehouse and logistics capacity planning.

Financial Planning  
Revenue forecasts are used for financial projections.

## Integration with Inventory Decision Engine

Demand forecasts serve as a key input for the Inventory Decision Engine.

The forecasting platform provides demand projections that power:

• automatic replenishment decisions  
• smart buying recommendations  
• inventory allocation across stores  
• ageing detection and pricing actions  

Together, these systems enable automated inventory management across large commerce platforms.
